WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:11.810 align:middle line:90%


00:00:11.810 --> 00:00:14.810 align:middle line:84%
>> I'm going to start you off
with a quote from Lao Tzu.

00:00:14.810 --> 00:00:18.500 align:middle line:84%
He said, "Those who
flow as life flows know

00:00:18.500 --> 00:00:21.888 align:middle line:90%
they need no other force."

00:00:21.888 --> 00:00:24.810 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:24.810 --> 00:00:32.119 align:middle line:90%


00:00:32.119 --> 00:00:33.620 align:middle line:90%
Welcome back.

00:00:33.620 --> 00:00:37.580 align:middle line:10%
Today we're talking about
the flow state and shamanism.

00:00:37.580 --> 00:00:41.650 align:middle line:10%
So my favorite book on flow
is called "Stealing Fire."

00:00:41.650 --> 00:00:44.480 align:middle line:10%
And the authors Jamie
Wheal and Steven Kotler

00:00:44.480 --> 00:00:48.580 align:middle line:10%
founded what is called
the Flow Genome Project.

00:00:48.580 --> 00:00:50.350 align:middle line:84%
I believe that the
Flow Genome Project

00:00:50.350 --> 00:00:53.980 align:middle line:84%
is looking deeper into
flow and studying it more

00:00:53.980 --> 00:00:56.860 align:middle line:90%
than anybody else ever has.

00:00:56.860 --> 00:01:00.460 align:middle line:84%
Flow state, this zone,
is very well-documented.

00:01:00.460 --> 00:01:03.340 align:middle line:10%
You'll have athletes like Bill
Russell and Michael Jordan

00:01:03.340 --> 00:01:06.370 align:middle line:10%
consistently talking about
experiencing this zone

00:01:06.370 --> 00:01:09.430 align:middle line:10%
during high intensity games.

00:01:09.430 --> 00:01:13.150 align:middle line:84%
Even musicians, rock
bands, and orchestras

00:01:13.150 --> 00:01:16.780 align:middle line:84%
all mention that there seems
to be this higher organizing

00:01:16.780 --> 00:01:19.660 align:middle line:84%
force that everybody
else simply surrenders

00:01:19.660 --> 00:01:22.570 align:middle line:84%
to when the music
becomes that one

00:01:22.570 --> 00:01:25.270 align:middle line:84%
thing that all the
rest of the musicians

00:01:25.270 --> 00:01:27.850 align:middle line:90%
are simply the conduit for.

00:01:27.850 --> 00:01:30.680 align:middle line:84%
The music is coming
through them.

00:01:30.680 --> 00:01:33.790 align:middle line:84%
But it's not just for
athletes and musicians.

00:01:33.790 --> 00:01:36.880 align:middle line:84%
It's actually even
good in the workplace.

00:01:36.880 --> 00:01:40.060 align:middle line:10%
There was a 10-year study from
the "McKinsey" magazine that

00:01:40.060 --> 00:01:44.710 align:middle line:10%
said top-level executives become
five times more productive

00:01:44.710 --> 00:01:46.390 align:middle line:10%
when in the state of flow.

00:01:46.390 --> 00:01:49.810 align:middle line:10%
It also crops up in
spiritual states.

00:01:49.810 --> 00:01:53.570 align:middle line:84%
There is this feeling of oneness
in the spiritual traditions

00:01:53.570 --> 00:01:57.490 align:middle line:84%
and this ability to be
able to access information.

00:01:57.490 --> 00:02:00.550 align:middle line:84%
And the actions that need to
happen from that point forward

00:02:00.550 --> 00:02:02.390 align:middle line:90%
are effortless.

00:02:02.390 --> 00:02:05.350 align:middle line:84%
So now let's go to the guy
who coined the term flow

00:02:05.350 --> 00:02:06.640 align:middle line:90%
and flow state.

00:02:06.640 --> 00:02:08.960 align:middle line:10%
His name is Mihaly
Csikszentmihalyi.

00:02:08.960 --> 00:02:12.280 align:middle line:10%
And he was studying flow
for quite some time.

00:02:12.280 --> 00:02:16.210 align:middle line:10%
And he said in regards
to extreme situations,

00:02:16.210 --> 00:02:19.180 align:middle line:10%
"You know what you need
to do is possible to do

00:02:19.180 --> 00:02:23.890 align:middle line:10%
even though difficult. And
the sense of time disappears.

00:02:23.890 --> 00:02:25.720 align:middle line:10%
You forget yourself.

00:02:25.720 --> 00:02:29.770 align:middle line:10%
And you feel part of
something larger."

00:02:29.770 --> 00:02:33.710 align:middle line:84%
This truly does sound spiritual,
this losing of one's self,

00:02:33.710 --> 00:02:37.450 align:middle line:84%
a disintegrating and merging
with the entire universe where

00:02:37.450 --> 00:02:40.600 align:middle line:84%
you are no longer
this little person,

00:02:40.600 --> 00:02:43.480 align:middle line:84%
but you are the entire
universe and the mind at large.

00:02:43.480 --> 00:02:48.410 align:middle line:90%


00:02:48.410 --> 00:02:50.500 align:middle line:84%
So if you think that
the state isn't for you,

00:02:50.500 --> 00:02:52.720 align:middle line:84%
it's only for
top-level athletes,

00:02:52.720 --> 00:02:54.670 align:middle line:84%
only for musicians
who have trained

00:02:54.670 --> 00:02:56.950 align:middle line:84%
their entire lives
or Navy SEALs,

00:02:56.950 --> 00:03:00.190 align:middle line:84%
people who have put their
entire lives into accessing

00:03:00.190 --> 00:03:01.540 align:middle line:90%
this state.

00:03:01.540 --> 00:03:05.200 align:middle line:84%
Well, remember what Johann
Wolfgang von Goethe said.

00:03:05.200 --> 00:03:08.337 align:middle line:84%
"Everything is hard
before it is easy."

00:03:08.337 --> 00:03:10.420 align:middle line:84%
But this doesn't mean that
we don't have obstacles

00:03:10.420 --> 00:03:11.380 align:middle line:90%
to the flow state.

00:03:11.380 --> 00:03:16.210 align:middle line:84%
All of us are very overwhelmed,
overworked, and exhausted.

00:03:16.210 --> 00:03:19.420 align:middle line:84%
We are what Steven Kotler, one
of the authors of "Stealing

00:03:19.420 --> 00:03:23.130 align:middle line:84%
Fire," calls 21st
century normal.

00:03:23.130 --> 00:03:26.410 align:middle line:84%
And when he describes what
21st century normal is,

00:03:26.410 --> 00:03:30.590 align:middle line:84%
he goes into what you can see
in the body physiologically.

00:03:30.590 --> 00:03:34.900 align:middle line:84%
So he says that hyperactivity
in the prefrontal cortex

00:03:34.900 --> 00:03:36.760 align:middle line:90%
comes online.

00:03:36.760 --> 00:03:39.020 align:middle line:84%
This is the higher cognitive
function of the brain,

00:03:39.020 --> 00:03:41.730 align:middle line:84%
our sense of morality,
and our sense of our will.

00:03:41.730 --> 00:03:44.950 align:middle line:84%
Our brainwaves go
into the beta state.

00:03:44.950 --> 00:03:48.580 align:middle line:84%
And then we have a steady
drip, drip of a stress hormone

00:03:48.580 --> 00:03:52.360 align:middle line:84%
called cortisol and another
one, norepinephrine.

00:03:52.360 --> 00:03:56.180 align:middle line:84%
But he goes on to say
that in the flow state,

00:03:56.180 --> 00:03:58.570 align:middle line:84%
the hyperactivity in
the prefrontal cortex,

00:03:58.570 --> 00:04:02.470 align:middle line:84%
that more human aspect
of our brain, goes quiet.

00:04:02.470 --> 00:04:06.610 align:middle line:84%
And therefore, so does
the inner critic within.

00:04:06.610 --> 00:04:10.510 align:middle line:84%
And then all of those
stressful hormones flush out.

00:04:10.510 --> 00:04:13.390 align:middle line:84%
And then we are flooded
with performance-enhancing

00:04:13.390 --> 00:04:17.649 align:middle line:84%
and also feel good hormones
like oxytocin, anandamide,

00:04:17.649 --> 00:04:22.100 align:middle line:90%
serotonin, and dopamine.

00:04:22.100 --> 00:04:24.640 align:middle line:84%
So the quieting of
this inner critic

00:04:24.640 --> 00:04:26.470 align:middle line:90%
is well-documented as well.

00:04:26.470 --> 00:04:28.080 align:middle line:84%
Michael Jordan is
one of those who

00:04:28.080 --> 00:04:30.520 align:middle line:90%
has talked about this state.

00:04:30.520 --> 00:04:32.650 align:middle line:84%
Michael Jordan also
is known as saying,

00:04:32.650 --> 00:04:36.520 align:middle line:84%
"Heart is what separates
the good from the great."

00:04:36.520 --> 00:04:39.220 align:middle line:84%
So let's take a
deeper look at heart.

00:04:39.220 --> 00:04:43.030 align:middle line:84%
Let's take a look at an episode
of "On the Road with Lilou"

00:04:43.030 --> 00:04:46.210 align:middle line:84%
where she interviews Howard
Martin in an episode called

00:04:46.210 --> 00:04:48.370 align:middle line:90%
At the Heart of it All.

00:04:48.370 --> 00:04:51.640 align:middle line:10%
>> So in the coherent state,
you have this highly-ordered

00:04:51.640 --> 00:04:55.240 align:middle line:10%
physiological and emotional
condition in yourself.

00:04:55.240 --> 00:04:58.600 align:middle line:10%
So everything from reaction
speed time to visual field,

00:04:58.600 --> 00:05:00.630 align:middle line:10%
all your sensitivities
are there.

00:05:00.630 --> 00:05:02.380 align:middle line:10%
You're more sensitive
to your environment.

00:05:02.380 --> 00:05:04.000 align:middle line:10%
You're more sensitive
to yourself.

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:05.950 align:middle line:84%
You're more sensitive
to what's going on.

00:05:05.950 --> 00:05:07.780 align:middle line:84%
You have a greater
ability to choose.

00:05:07.780 --> 00:05:10.630 align:middle line:10%
You have a greater ability
to regulate your emotions.

00:05:10.630 --> 00:05:13.793 align:middle line:10%
Athletes equate that to
what happens in the zone.

00:05:13.793 --> 00:05:16.210 align:middle line:10%
So the measurement of coherence
is the closest measurement

00:05:16.210 --> 00:05:18.910 align:middle line:10%
that we know of to
measuring the zone.

00:05:18.910 --> 00:05:20.860 align:middle line:10%
So we've worked with
professional golfers,

00:05:20.860 --> 00:05:23.440 align:middle line:10%
professional football
players, Olympic athletes

00:05:23.440 --> 00:05:27.700 align:middle line:10%
of various kinds, gymnasts,
skiers, swimmers, all kinds.

00:05:27.700 --> 00:05:30.970 align:middle line:10%
And they use our technology
and our simple techniques

00:05:30.970 --> 00:05:34.960 align:middle line:10%
to find a way to develop more
of that coherence in themselves

00:05:34.960 --> 00:05:38.320 align:middle line:10%
naturally so that when they're
in athletic performance,

00:05:38.320 --> 00:05:40.300 align:middle line:10%
it becomes second nature
to them because they

00:05:40.300 --> 00:05:41.925 align:middle line:10%
can't think about
all that when they're

00:05:41.925 --> 00:05:43.960 align:middle line:10%
in the middle of
a football game.

00:05:43.960 --> 00:05:46.530 align:middle line:90%


00:05:46.530 --> 00:05:47.570 align:middle line:90%
>> So that's great.

00:05:47.570 --> 00:05:49.760 align:middle line:84%
There's two aspects
of what you just

00:05:49.760 --> 00:05:52.020 align:middle line:84%
heard that I would
like to point back out.

00:05:52.020 --> 00:05:58.420 align:middle line:84%
One is that coherence sounds
an awful lot like flow.

00:05:58.420 --> 00:06:01.070 align:middle line:84%
And number two is
that in this state,

00:06:01.070 --> 00:06:05.060 align:middle line:84%
information is organized
and ordered differently.

00:06:05.060 --> 00:06:09.780 align:middle line:84%
So that is a hallmark of an
altered state of consciousness.

00:06:09.780 --> 00:06:14.450 align:middle line:84%
Now, what if we could access
coherence or flow on demand?

00:06:14.450 --> 00:06:16.400 align:middle line:84%
What if we could just
call it up in the most

00:06:16.400 --> 00:06:19.170 align:middle line:84%
unlikely or difficult
circumstances?

00:06:19.170 --> 00:06:23.040 align:middle line:84%
So in gaming terms, this
would be called leveling up.

00:06:23.040 --> 00:06:25.070 align:middle line:90%
So how do we access flow?

00:06:25.070 --> 00:06:28.610 align:middle line:84%
Well, if we go back to
Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi,

00:06:28.610 --> 00:06:31.100 align:middle line:84%
he not only studied flow
more than anybody else,

00:06:31.100 --> 00:06:33.350 align:middle line:90%
he coined that term flow.

00:06:33.350 --> 00:06:34.970 align:middle line:84%
But he also
identified that there

00:06:34.970 --> 00:06:38.960 align:middle line:84%
are three triggers to flow
that we can use in our lives

00:06:38.960 --> 00:06:40.850 align:middle line:90%
right now immediately.

00:06:40.850 --> 00:06:45.110 align:middle line:84%
And these three triggers
are having clear goals,

00:06:45.110 --> 00:06:47.540 align:middle line:84%
immediate feedback
from the challenge,

00:06:47.540 --> 00:06:51.710 align:middle line:84%
and also the proper
skill to challenge ratio.

00:06:51.710 --> 00:06:54.290 align:middle line:84%
Now clear goals are
knowing what I'm doing now

00:06:54.290 --> 00:06:57.650 align:middle line:84%
and what I'm going to do next
so the mind does not wander.

00:06:57.650 --> 00:07:01.400 align:middle line:84%
Immediate feedback is important
so we can change directions

00:07:01.400 --> 00:07:03.620 align:middle line:90%
if need be in the moment.

00:07:03.620 --> 00:07:07.080 align:middle line:84%
Skill to challenge
ratio is very specific.

00:07:07.080 --> 00:07:10.460 align:middle line:84%
It's actually if here
is your skill level,

00:07:10.460 --> 00:07:15.440 align:middle line:84%
then 4% above your skill
level is the optimal range

00:07:15.440 --> 00:07:16.640 align:middle line:90%
to trigger flow.

00:07:16.640 --> 00:07:20.060 align:middle line:84%
So you want the challenge to
be just outside of your skill

00:07:20.060 --> 00:07:22.160 align:middle line:84%
level, meaning this is
something that you have

00:07:22.160 --> 00:07:23.720 align:middle line:90%
to rise to the occasion for.

00:07:23.720 --> 00:07:28.310 align:middle line:84%
You need to reach to
arrive at this skill

00:07:28.310 --> 00:07:29.850 align:middle line:90%
to meet that challenge.

00:07:29.850 --> 00:07:33.390 align:middle line:84%
And then if these three
are done correctly,

00:07:33.390 --> 00:07:38.830 align:middle line:84%
it will prompt that state of
flow or coherence on demand.

00:07:38.830 --> 00:07:42.530 align:middle line:84%
But what is it that gets in
the way of us even setting out

00:07:42.530 --> 00:07:45.290 align:middle line:90%
on that path of training?

00:07:45.290 --> 00:07:48.080 align:middle line:84%
Even in the tasks that we
would love to train for,

00:07:48.080 --> 00:07:51.140 align:middle line:84%
what keeps us from being
able to just set out

00:07:51.140 --> 00:07:55.400 align:middle line:84%
on the path of discovering and
unlocking our human potential?

00:07:55.400 --> 00:07:59.210 align:middle line:84%
Well, could it be the
fear of the unknown?

00:07:59.210 --> 00:08:02.060 align:middle line:84%
Let's take a look at a
film called "Beyond Fear"

00:08:02.060 --> 00:08:05.580 align:middle line:90%
by Louie Schwartzberg.

